quot%3BEven%20just%20having%20a%20police%20car%20parked%20outside%20can%20make%20people%20think%20twice%20about%20shoplifting%20from%20our%20branches%2C%20or%20becoming%20aggressive%20towards%20our%20Partners%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicki%20Juniper%2C%20John%20Lewis%20Partnership's%20head%20of%20security%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Lewis%20Partnership%20said%20it%20had%20already%20increased%20the%20number%20of%20guards%20and%20staff%20who%20have%20been%20trained%20to%20stop%20and%20detain%20offenders%2C%20improved%20CCTV%2C%20and%20offered%20body-worn%20cameras%20to%20staff.%20It's%20trialing%20increasing%20the%20number%20of%20security%2C%20warning%20customers%20that%20CCTV%20is%20in%20use%20and%20that%20shoplifters%20face%20jail%20time.%20Waitrose%20has%20also%20trained%20staff%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thegrocer.co.uk%2Fwaitrose%2Fwaitrose-looks-to-deter-shoplifters-with-in-store-love-bombing%2F680912.article%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Blove-bombing%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20described%20as%20being%20extra%20attentive%20to%20customers%2C%20including%20asking%20if%20they%20needed%20help%20at%20self-service%20checkouts%2C%20to%20deter%20theft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20while%20many%20of%20these%20efforts%20have%20been%20effective%20in%20stopping%20individual%20shoplifters%2C%20retailers%20are%20increasingly%20dealing%20with%20groups%20and%20organised%20crime%2C%20which%20can%20only%20be%20tackled%20with%20wider%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Lewis%20Partnership%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20assaults%20on%20employees%20at%20Waitrose%20stores%20has%20roughly%20doubled%20since%202020%2C%20The%20Times%20reported.%20This%20rise%20was%20driven%20by%20%26quot%3Bprofessional%20shoplifters%20stealing%20for%20greed%2C%26quot%3B%20Juniper%20told%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollectively%2C%20British%20retailers%20recorded%20on%20average%20more%20than%20850%20incidents%20of%20violence%20and%20abuse%20against%20workers%20a%20day%20in%20the%20year%20to%20March%2031%2C%202022%2C%20including%20racial%20and%20sexual%20abuse%2C%20physical%20assault%2C%20and%20threats%20with%20weapons%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrc.org.uk%2Fnews%2Foperations%2Fbrc-crime-survey-2023%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBRC%2520survey%2520shows%2520high%2520levels%2Cmillion%2520incidents%2520in%25202021%252F22%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20British%20Retail%20Consortium%20found.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BRC%20said%20that%20though%20this%20was%20slightly%20down%20on%20the%20previous%20year's%20figures%2C%20it%20was%20almost%20double%20the%20rate%20prior%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20represented%20105%20incidents%20per%201%2C000%20store%20workers.%20Significantly%20fewer%20incidents%20were%20reported%20to%20police%20than%20the%20prior%20year%2C%20which%20the%20BRC%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Blargely%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20confidence%20in%20any%20police%20response.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BRC%20found%20that%20in%20the%20year%20to%20March%2031%2C%202022%2C%20retailers%20lost%20%C2%A31.04%20billion%2C%20or%20%241.32%20billion%2C%20to%20retail%20crime%2C%20including%20%C2%A3953%20million%20to%20customer%20theft%2C%20and%20spent%20around%20%C2%A3722%20million%20on%20crime%20prevention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparate%20data%20from%20police%20forces%20in%20England%2C%20Wales%2C%20and%20Northern%20Ireland%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-65764513%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalyzed%20by%20BBC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20nearly%2033%2C000%20recorded%20incidents%20of%20shoplifting%20in%20March%2C%20a%20jump%20of%20nearly%20a%20third%20compared%20to%20March%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20retailers%20have%20attempted%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20retail%20crime%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forganized-retail-crime-top-items-criminals-are-looking-to-st