22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fplanet-earth%2Fgeology%2Ffountains-of-diamonds-erupt-from-earths-center-as-supercontinents-break-up%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E80%20miles%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20powerful%20eruptions%2C%20and%20what%20triggered%20them%2C%20have%20long%20baffled%20scientists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%20%26quot%3Bwhy%20on%20Earth%20do%20they%20shoot%20up%20from%20the%20deep%20after%20spending%20potentially%20billions%20of%20years%20sat%20there%3F%26quot%3B%20Tom%20Ger%20non%2C%20a%20geologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southampton%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2F2023%2Fjul%2F26%2Fwhy-do-diamonds-erupt-earth-depths-scientists-have-answer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20led%20a%20study%20on%20the%20topic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20researchers%20think%20they%20have%20an%20explanation.%C2%A0Based%20on%20computer%20models%2C%20they%20believe%20these%20eruptions%20may%20have%20been%20triggered%20by%20the%20breakup%20of%20supercontinents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%2C%20they%20claim%2C%20could%20help%20miners%20in%20their%20search%20for%20undiscovered%20diamond%20deposits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDiamonds%20can%20erupt%20to%20the%20surface%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20known%20for%20some%20time%20that%20a%20special%20form%20of%20magma%20called%20kimberlite%20can%20rip%20through%20the%20Earth's%20core%20at%20staggering%20speeds%20carrying%20diamonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20magma%20is%20rich%20in%20gases%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20water.%20That%20propels%20it%20from%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20Earth%2C%20like%20soda%20gushing%20from%20a%20bottle%20that%20has%20been%20shaken%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20magma%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiamond-planets-could-exist-in-universe-new-research-2020-9%5C%22%3Epick%20up%20diamonds%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20the%20way%20as%20it%20bubbles%20to%20the%20surface.%20This%20creates%20diamond-rich%20areas%2C%20that%20are%20ripe%20for%20mining.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20dark%20rock%20spotted%20with%20while%20specs%20shown%20here%20is%20a%20diamond-bearing%20kimberlite%20seen%20in%20Yellowknife%2C%20Northwest%20Territories%20in%20Canada%20September%2026%2C%202015.%20%20REUTERS%2FSusan%20Taylor%2FFile%20Photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e336cbb698ac0019ddea50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20is%20what%20diamonds%20look%20like%20when%20they%20are%20trapped%20in%20kimberlite.%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20you're%20thinking%20of%20planning%20your%20next%20holiday%20to%20see%20a%20diamond%20eruption%2C%20think%20again.%20No%20human%20in%20history%20has%20seen%20one%20of%20these%20happen%2C%20and%20that's%20because%20these%20tend%20to%20happen%20near%20a%20time%20of%20great%20continental%20disruption%2C%20like%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpangea-split-apart-way-faster-than-we-thought-2016-7%5C%22%3EPangaea%20broke%3C%2Fa%3E%20apart%20about%20200%20million%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20eruption%20of%20this%20kind%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20taken%20place%2011%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Guardian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pattern%20of%20diamond%20eruptions%20is%20cyclical%2C%20mimicking%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.southampton.ac.uk%2Fnews%2F2023%2F07%2Fdiamond-eruptions.page%5C%22%3Erhythm%20of%20the%20supercontinents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20assemble%20and%20break%20up%20in%20a%20repeated%20pattern%20over%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Gernon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20scientists%20found%20that%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findia-potential-natural-diamond-trove-2013-8%2F%5C%22%3Ekimberlite%20volcanoes%3C%2Fa%3E%20occurred%2020%20to%2030%20million%20years%20after%20the%20tectonic%20breakup%20of%20Earth's%20continents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20continental%20divide%20stretches%20the%20Earth's%20crust%20like%20pizza%20dough%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20would%20expect%20the%20kimberlite%20to%20erupt%20near%20the%20borders%20of%20the%20continent%2C%20where%20the%20plates%20are%20being%20ripped%20apart%20by%20the%20continental%20divide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20instead%2C%20it%20tends%20to%20appear%20in%20%26quot%3Ba%20sweet%20spot%20in%20the%20interior%20of%20continents%20where%20diamonds%20form%2C%26quot%3B%20Gernon%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20analyzing%20the%20eruptions%20more%20closely%2C%20scientists%20think%20they've%20cracked%20this%20mystery.%20And%20it's%20down%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bdomino%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20churns%20the%20kimberlite%20closer%20and%20closer%20to%20the%20center%20of%20continents%2C%20Stephen%20Jones%2C%20co-author%20on%20the%20study%20and%20Professor%20of%20geology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Birmingham%2C%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20continents%20are%20pulled%20apart%20by%20the%20divide%2C%20it%20stretches%20the%20Earth's%20crust%20like%20a%20pizza%20dough.%20That%20thinning%20causes%20the%20crust%20to%20sink%20into%20the%20Earth's%20mantle%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20interaction%20rips%20off%20big%20chunks%20of%20the%20rock%20from%20the%20continental%20plate.%20As%20these%20drop%20into%20the%20mantle%2C%20they%20drive%20a%20churning%20motion%20beneath%20the%20continent%2C%20said%20Jones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRemarkably%2C%20this%20process%20brings%20together%20the%20necessary%20ingredients%20in%20the%20right%20amounts%20to%20trigger%20just%20enough%20melting%20to%20generate%20kimberlites%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gernon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221820%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20huge%20pit%20next%20to%20a%20neighboring%20town%20is%20a%20diamond%20mine%20in%20Russia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e336dfb698ac0019ddea6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20diamond%20mine%20in%20Russia.%3Cp%3ESergei%20Karpukhin%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20say%20having%20uncovered%20this%20chain%20reaction%20could%20help%20discover%20diamond%20deposits%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20also%20shows%20how%20the%20Earth's%20interior%20interacts%20with%20the%20Earth's%20surface%20%E2%80%94%20and%20notably%20how%20it%20could%20interact%20with%20our%20environment%20and%20the%20climate%2C%20said%20Gernon%20who%20says%20he'll%20be%20studying%20this%20relationship%20more%20closely.%20The%20diamonds%20in%20the%20kimberlite%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bmight%20be%20just%20a%20part%20of%20the%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gernon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D1460f5ddcdfa3372d397c1e5070e2b66bb82eed0e1b1c9bc7c45755481734acb%26postID%3D64e31e38328d007bfe701772%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-023-06193-3.epdf%5C%22%3Epeer-reviewed%20journal%20Nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20July%2026.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffountains-diamonds-erupt-from-ground-when-continents-break-up-study-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692618708000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e329bdb698ac0019dde170%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffountains-diamonds-erupt-from-ground-when-continents-break-up-study-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Diamonds%20erupt%20from%20deep%20underground%20onto%20Earth's%20surface%20during%20volcani