property%20was%20put%20on%20the%20block%20on%20Sunday%20by%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20to%20recover%20Rs%2056%20crore%20through%20an%20e-auction%20to%20be%20held%20on%20August%2025.%20The%20Gurdaspur%20MP%20has%20been%20in%20default%20on%20a%20Rs%2055.99%20crore%20loan%20from%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20since%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCorrigendum%20to%20e-auction%20notice%20with%20regards%20to%20sale%20auction%20notice%20in%20respect%20of%20Mr%20Ajay%20Singh%20Deol%20alias%20Mr%20Sunny%20Deol%20stands%20withdrawn%20due%20to%20technical%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20today.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20had%20said%20on%20Sunday%20that%20the%20auction%20of%20the%20Juhu%20property%20known%20as%20Sunny%20Villa%20would%20commence%20at%20Rs%2051.43%20crore.%20The%20minimum%20bid%20amount%20was%20set%20at%20Rs%205.14%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692617700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fhmpps5fo_sunny-deol_625x300_20_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbank-of-baroda-explains-why-it-withdrew-sunny-deols-bungalow-auction-notice-4315919%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20auction%20notice%20for%20actor%20and%20BJP%20MP%20Sunny%20Deol's%20bungalow%20in%20Mumbai's%20Juhu%20was%20withdrawn%20due%20to%20technical%20reasons%2C%20the%20state-owned%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20said%20today%2C%20and%20revealed%20the%20actor%20has%20approached%20the%20bank%20to%20settle%20dues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbank-of-baroda-explains-why-it-withdrew-sunny-deols-bungalow-auction-notice-4315919%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbank-of-baroda-explains-why-it-withdrew-sunny-deols-bungalow-auction-notice-4315919%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbank-of-baroda-explains-why-it-withdrew-sunny-deols-bungalow-auction-notice-4315919%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Why%20Made%20In%20Heaven's%20Dalit%20Wedding%20Is%20More%20Radical%20Than%20You%20Think%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWith%20much%20talked%20about%20episode%205%20of%20%3Cem%3EMade%20in%20Heaven%202%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Neeraj%20Ghaywan%20redefines%20the%20discourse%20on%20caste%20in%20mainstream%20Hindi%20filmmaking.%20While%20many%20films%20dealing%20with%20the%20theme%20of%20caste%20prejudices%20have%20been%20made%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20almost%20all%20of%20them%20approach%20caste%20as%20a%20system%20of%20discrimination%20and%20place%20their%20hopes%20in%20modernity%20and%20a%20mirage%20of%20a%20casteless%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20episode%20is%20radical%20because%20it%20questions%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20a%20casteless%20society%2C%20as%20it%20demands%20adherence%20to%20upper-caste%20norms%20and%20the%20erasure%20of%20the%20Dalit%20past.%20Instead%20of%20advocating%20Dalits%20joining%20the%20mainstream%20by%20forgetting%20their%20past%2C%20it%20asks%20for%20the%20reclamation%20of%20history%20and%20its%20celebration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22u3emota4%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fu3emota4_embed1_625x300_21_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EA%20still%20from%20%3Cem%3EMade%20In%20Heaven%202%3A%20The%20Heart%20Skipped%20A%20Beat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeeraj%20Ghaywan%20has%20consistently%20made%20films%20on%20Dalit%20themes%2C%20and%20with%20his%20career%2C%20the%20discourse%20around%20Dalit%20issues%20has%20also%20evolved.%20Tracing%20his%20cinematic%20work%2C%20one%20can%20also%20see%20a%20journey%20of%20the%20theme%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2015)%2C%20Ghaywan's%20debut%20film%2C%20traces%20the%20journey%20of%20a%20Dalit%20boy%20and%20an%20upper%20caste%20girl.%20Both%20of%20them%20escape%20an%20oppressive%20society%20that%20thrives%20on%20the%20ideas%20of%20caste%20and%20honour.%20Their%20employment%20with%20the%20Railways%2C%20the%20vehicle%20of%20modernity%2C%20brings%20them%20to%20Allahabad%20(now%2C%20Prayagraj)%2C%20the%20city%20of%20confluence%2C%20and%20the%20film%20ends%20on%20a%20feel-good%20note%20where%20caste%20seems%20to%20have%20gotten%20irrelevant%20because%20none%20of%20the%20characters%20practises%20their%20caste-based%20occupations.%20As%20migrant%20workers%20of%20modernity%2C%20they%20are%20in%20the%20same%20boat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ending%20of%20Masaan%20is%20feelgood%20because%20it%20assumes%20that%20once%20people%20from%20different%20castes%20get%20employed%20in%20modern%20workplaces%20such%20as%20railways%2C%20caste-based%20prejudices%20will%20cease%20to%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhaywan%20revisits%20this%20assumption%20in%20his%20short%2C%20%3Cem%3EGeeli%20Puchi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Part%20of%20the%202021%20Netflix%20anthology%20%3Cem%3EAjeeb%20Daastaan%3C%2Fem%3Es).%20Here%2C%20two%20women%20work%20in%20a%20modern%20factory%2C%20but%20still%2C%20the%20Dalit%20woman%20faces%20discrimination%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20career%20advancement.%20Though%20the%20film%20intricately%20tells%20the%20stories%20of%20the%20central%20characters%2C%20Ghaywan%20scrutinises%20his%20earlier%20assumption%20and%20offers%20a%20new%20finding.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20upper%20castes%20own%20the%20means%20of%20production%2C%20the%20Dalit%20workers%20will%20continue%20to%20face%20discrimination%20unless%20they%20learn%20the%20shrewdness%20of%20the%20upper%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20much%20talked%20about%20fifth%20episode%20of%20%3Cem%3EMade%20in%20Heaven%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20takes%20us%20into%20the%20future%20and%20scrutinises%20the%20assumption%20that%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20made%2C%20just%20that%20genders%20are%20reversed%2C%20and%20the%20class%20difference%20has%20narrowed.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20casteless%20society%20of%20the%20USA%2C%20a%20Dalit%20woman%20and%20an%20upper-caste%20man%20fall%20in%20love%20and%20decide%20to%20get%20married.%20So%20far%2C%20so%20good%2C%20as%20there%20are%20no%20raised%20eyebrows%20of%20parents%2C%20no%20elopement%20or%20honour%20killing.%20Everything%20goes%20without%20a%20glitch%20until%20the%20ritual%20of%20marriage%20is%20discussed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Dalit%20girl%20doesn't%20want%20a%20Brahmanical%20ritualistic%20marriage%2C%20and%20the%20man%20is%20okay%20with%20it%2C%20but%20his%20family%20isn't.%20They%20want%20a%20brief%20ritual%20of%20%3Cem%3Ephera%3C%2Fem%3Es%20after%20the%20registration%20of%20the%20marriage.%20When%20the%20girl%20asserts%20and%20wants%20to%20have%20a%20Dalit%20Buddhist%20wedding%20to%20follow%20the%20%3Cem%3Ephera%3C%2Fem%3Es%2C%20the%20family%20tries%20many%20tricks%20to%20get%20her%20to%20drop%20the%20idea.%20Even%20worse%2C%20her%20groom-to-be%20fails%20to%20empathise%20with%20her.%20The%20episode%20ends%20with%20the%20upper%20caste%20man's%20realisation%20of%20his%20family's%20hidden%20prejudices%20against%20the%20girl's%20assertion%20of%20her%20identity.%20And%20finally%2C%20Ghaywan%20shows%20us%20what%20a%20Dalit%20wedding%20could%20look%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22dlvid0js%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fdlvid0js_embed_625x300_21_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EA%20still%20from%20%3Cem%3EMade%20In%20Heaven%202%3A%20The%20Heart%20Skipped%20A%20Beat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20episode%20re-examines%20some%20of%20the%20assumptions%20on%20which%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20ends.%20Will%20caste%20still%20matter%20in%20a%20casteless%20society%3F%20The%20answer%20that%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20brings%20forth%20is%3A%20%26quot%3Bmaybe%26quot%3B.%20But%2C%20Ghaywan%20revises%20the%20answer%20in%20the%20episode%20and%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20caste%20still%20matters%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20rituals%20of%20marriage%20if%20not%20marriage%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20equality%20is%20revisited%2C%20too.%20Will%20caste%20cease%20to%20matter%20if%20people%20take%20up%20modern%20professions%3F%20And%2C%20when%20the%20economic%20class%20difference%20narrows%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20that%20the%20episode%20presents%20is%20very%20different%20from%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E's.%20Episode%205%20is%20politically%20more%20complex%20as%20it%20shows%20how%20problematic%20slogans%20such%20as%20bringing%20Dalits%20into%20the%20mainstream%20is.%20It%20means%20acceptance%20only%20as%20long%20as%20Dalits%20live%20in%20denial%20of%20their%20past%20and%20assume%20the%20codes%20of%20upper%20castes.%20However%2C%20when%20a%20Dalit%20person%20asserts%20her%20identity%20and%20demands%20a%20celebration%20of%20her%20heritage%2C%20it%20makes%20the%20upper%20caste%20household%20uncomfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20episode%20is%20important%20because%20it%20proclaims%20a%20significant%20departure%20in%20Dalit%20discourse%20in%20mainstream%20Hindi%20filmmaking%2C%20from%20the%20portrayal%20of%20oppression%20to%20the%20assertion%20of%20identity.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20a%20catch%20that%20the%20episode%20captures%20beautifully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20bride-to-be%20asserts%20her%20Dalit%20identity%20unapologetically%2C%20her%20family%2C%20particularly%20her%20younger%20brother%2C%20holds%20it%20against%20her.%20Why%3F%20He%20says%20he%20won't%20like%20being%20identified%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bquota%20student%26quot%3B%20in%20his%20college.%20So%2C%20the%20assertion%20is%20a%20path%20fraught%20with%20risks%2C%20like%20it%20is%20for%20the%20brother%20in%20a%20caste-ridden%20society%20like%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20episode%2C%20Ghaywan%20busts%20the%20myth%20of%20the%20mainstream%20and%20defines%20it%20as%20an%20idea%20of%20cultural%20subjugation.%20Instead%20of%20seeking%20admission%20into%20the%20mainstream%20by%20accepting%20Brahmanical%20rituals%2C%20Ghaywan%20advocates%20the%20need%20for%20new%20symbols%20and%20new%20rituals.%20And%2C%20who%20better%20to%20turn%20to%20for%20that%20than%20Buddha%20and%20Ambedkar%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ghaywan%20and%20the%20writers%20of%20the%20show%20Alankrita%20Shrivastava%2C%20Zoya%20Akhtar%2C%20Reema%20Kagti%20and%20additional%20writer%20Rahul%20Nair%20deserve%20all%20the%20credit%20for%20redefining%20the%20Dalit%20discourse%20into%20the%20mainstream%2C%20it's%20somewhat%20tragic%20that%20creators%20resorted%20to%20cold%20legality%20after%20Yashica%20Dutt%20(%3Cem%3EComing%20Out%20as%20Dalit%3A%20A%20Memoir%3C%2Fem%3E)%20demanded%20credit%20in%20the%20episode%20claiming%20that%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Dalit%20girl's%20character%20is%20based%20on%20her.%20Strangely%2C%20Ghaywan%20had%20even%20acknowledged%20her%20as%20an%20inspiration%20for%20the%20character%20(particularly%20the%20interview%20scene)%20before%20posting%20her%20demand's%20rebuttal%20on%20Instagram.%20One%20would%20have%20expected%20more%20grace%20and%20empathy%20from%20the%20creators%20of%20a%20show%20which%20successfully%20raises%20the%20issues%20of%20discrimination.%20Would%20it%20have%20hurt%20to%20acknowledge%20her%20contribution%20on%20the%20screen%20if%20they%20already%20did%20so%20on%20social%20media%3F%20Isn't%20the%20controversy%20essentially%20the%20same%20denial%20the%20episode%20claims%20to%20expose%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bikas%20Mishra%20is%20an%20award-winning%20writer-director%20based%20in%20Mumbai)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692617520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fi7g413f4_bikas240_120x90_03_July_23.jpg%3Fver-20230818.04%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fopinion-why-made-in-heavens-dalit-wedding-is-more-radical-than-you-thin