he%20US%20are%20proving%20important%20for%20stopping%20Russian%20attacks%20on%20its%20positions%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F08%2F21%2Fukraine-cluster-bombs-biden%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden's%20decision%20to%20send%20the%20weapons%20to%20Ukraine%20in%20July%20attracted%20criticism%2C%20with%20allies%20including%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20Canada%20expressing%20concern%20over%20potential%20civilian%20casualties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weapons%20differ%20from%20normal%20munitions%2C%20which%20land%20and%20create%20a%20single%20explosion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECluster%20munitions%20break%20apart%20above%20their%20target%2C%20dispersing%20large%20numbers%20of%20small%20bombs%20over%20a%20wide%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20smaller%20bombs%20often%20don't%20detonate%20properly%2C%20and%20can%20lie%20unexploded%20for%20years%2C%20posing%20a%20lasting%20threat%20to%20local%20populations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20officials%20told%20the%20Post%20that%20the%20weapons%20were%20having%20an%20important%20impact%20on%20the%20front%20line%2C%20helping%20to%20slow%20and%20deter%20Russian%20attacks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20benefit%20is%20that%20the%20enemy%20is%20now%20very%20scared%20to%20go%20on%20assault%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stanislav%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20military%20official%20whom%20The%20Post%20identified%20only%20by%20his%20call%20sign%20for%20security%20reasons.%20%26quot%3BThey%20even%20recognize%20the%20cluster%20bombs%20by%20the%20whistle%20they%20make%20when%20headed%20their%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Stanislav%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Biden%20agreed%20to%20Ukrainian%20requests%20for%20the%20weapons%2C%20analysts%20said%20their%20main%20use%20would%20be%20to%20help%20Ukraine%20break%20through%20Russia's%20formidable%20defenses%20as%20part%20of%20its%20counteroffensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20reported%20that%20they%20have%20been%20useful%20defensively%20too.%20While%20Ukraine%20is%20attacking%2C%20Russian%20troops%20can%20shelter%20in%20their%20trenches%20and%20avoid%20much%20of%20the%20damage.%20But%20if%20the%20Russians%20are%20advancing%20over%20open%20ground%2C%20then%20the%20weapons%20can%20be%20devastating.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20said%20the%20offensive%20use%20of%20the%20cluster%20munitions%20has%20been%20in%20pinning%20down%20Russian%20troops%2C%20meaning%20they%20stay%20sheltering%20as%20Ukraine%20advances.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Fukraine-apparent-russian-cluster-munition-attack%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Rand%20think%20tank%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20the%20munitions%20were%20especially%20useful%20given%20that%20Ukraine's%20regular%20artillery%20stocks%20were%20badly%20depleted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20100%20countries%20are%20signatories%20to%20the%20the%20Convention%20on%20Cluster%20Munitions%2C%20which%20bans%20the%20use%20and%20stockpiling%20of%20the%20weapon.%20US%20allies%20like%20the%20UK%2C%20Germany%20and%20France%20have%20agreed%20not%20the%20use%20them%2C%20but%20the%20US%2C%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20are%20not%20signatories%20of%20the%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20have%20used%20the%20munitions%20during%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Fukraine-apparent-russian-cluster-munition-attack%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20Russia%20accused%20of%20using%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20weapons%20in%20attacks%20on%20civilian%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-cluster-bomb-use-deters-russian-attacks-report-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv