fir-against-rahul-yadav-issues-lookout-notice-123082100371_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fmumbai-police-eow-lodges-fir-against-rahul-yadav-issues-lookout-notice-123082100371_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Home%20Ministry%20Officials%20Top%20List%20of%20Complaints%20Received%20By%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21132433%2FCentral-vigilance-commission-logo.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cvc.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FARR2022.pdf%5C%22%3Elatest%20annual%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20(CVC)%20said%20that%20home%20affairs%20ministry%20employees%20made%20up%20the%20largest%20target%20of%20complaints%20it%20received%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20a%20total%20of%201%2C15%2C203%20complaints%20it%20received%20against%20Union%20government%20employees%2C%20the%20CVC%20said%20that%2046%2C643%20(~41%25)%20were%20against%20home%20affairs%20ministry%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20railways%20sector%20was%20at%20a%20distant%20second%20with%2010%2C580%20(9%25)%20complaints%20against%20its%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBanks%E2%80%9D%20employees%20were%20a%20source%20of%208%2C129%20complaints%2C%20the%20Delhi%20government%20of%207%2C370%20and%20%E2%80%9CCoal%E2%80%9D%20of%204%2C304.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CVC%20is%20an%20apex%20anti-corruption%20agency%20that%20oversees%20the%20vigilance%20administration%20of%20Union%20government%20organisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESet%20up%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cvc.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Far2001.pdf%5C%22%3Espirit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cadministration%20%5Bcannot%5D%20be%20a%20judge%20of%20its%20own%20conduct%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20CVC%20is%20not%20controlled%20by%20any%20Union%20ministry%20and%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cvc.gov.in%2F%3Fq%3Dfaq%5C%22%3Eresponsible%20only%20to%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20functions%2C%20it%20provides%20%E2%80%98vigilance%20clearances%E2%80%99%20to%20certain%20senior%20government%20officials%20and%20processes%20complaints%20against%20government%20employees%2C%20following%20which%20it%20communicates%20its%20advice%20on%20action%20to%20be%20taken%20in%20appropriate%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20commission%20said%20in%20its%20most%20recent%20annual%20report%20that%20there%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20deviations%E2%80%9D%20or%20non-compliance%20with%20its%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20some%20cases%20of%20officers%20covered%20under%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction%2C%20either%20the%20prescribed%20consultation%20mechanism%20with%20the%20Commission%20was%20not%20adhered%20to%2C%20or%20the%20authorities%20concerned%20did%20not%20accept%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20stated%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20there%20have%20been%20instances%20where%20the%20advice%20tendered%20by%20the%20Commission%20has%20been%20substantially%20diluted%20without%20approaching%20the%20Commission%20for%20reconsideration%20of%20its%20advice%2C%20as%20per%20extant%20procedure%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20the%20CVC%20gave%20of%20improper%20following%20of%20procedure%20with%20its%20advice%20was%20the%20delaying%20of%20taking%20action%20against%20some%20delinquent%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20organisations%20take%20more%20than%20the%20prescribed%20time%20for%20implementation%20of%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%20which%20includes%20delay%20in%20issuance%20of%20charge%20sheet.%20Sometimes%2C%20the%20delinquent%20officer%20is%20allowed%20to%20retire%2C%20and%20the%20misconduct%20becomes%20time%20barred%20for%20initiation%20of%20departmental%20action%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20watchdog%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20appendices%20to%20its%20annual%20report%2C%20the%20commission%20recorded%20the%20type%20of%20punishment%20that%20was%20given%20to%20government%20employees%20from%20various%20sectors%20following%20penalty%20proceedings%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20Union%20home%20affairs%20ministry%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20that%20the%20following%20punishments%20were%20given%20to%20its%20employees%20after%20major%20penalty%20proceedings%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties-1024x477.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22666%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties-1024x477.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21131839%2FMHA-major-penalties.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668955%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20cvc.gov.in%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20majority%20of%20employees%20in%20these%20cases%20had%20no%20action%20taken%20against%20them%2C%20unspecified%20%E2%80%9Cmajor%20penalties%E2%80%9D%20handed%20out%2C%20or%20were%20given%20warnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20following%20are%20the%20results%20of%20minor%20proceedings%20against%20home%20affairs%20employees%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%