ary%20Jane%20Wilkie%20is%20an%20independent%20contractor%20for%20a%20recruiter%20who%20moved%20from%20NYC%20to%20Paris%20in%202021.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20began%20to%20dream%20of%20moving%20after%20making%20friends%20and%20visiting%20with%20her%20singing%20group%20in%202016.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20a%20few%20challenges%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20taxes%20and%20cultural%20differences%2C%20she%20loves%20her%20new%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20my%20fantasy%20to%20move%20to%20Paris%2C%20but%20not%20necessarily%20at%20age%2079%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20just%20when%20it%20happened.%20I'd%20lived%20in%20New%20York%20City%20for%2035%20years%2C%20but%20Paris%20had%20been%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECOVID-19%20quashed%20an%20earlier%20attempt%20to%20leave%20New%20York%20City%20in%20March%202020%2C%20so%20almost%20two%20years%20later%2C%20I%20boarded%20the%20plane%20shortly%20after%20my%2079th%20birthday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20than%2020%20years%2C%20I've%20worked%20as%20an%20independent%20contractor%20for%20a%20recruiter%2C%20conducting%20interviews%20with%20candidates%20for%20executive%20positions%20with%20a%20national%20nonprofit%20organization.%20Because%20I%20could%20carry%20the%20work%20with%20me%20from%20the%20US%2C%20I%20still%20do%20this%20in%20Paris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20chose%20Paris%20for%20a%20few%20reasons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20spent%20about%20half%20of%20my%20adult%20years%20enjoying%20New%20York%20City%2C%20I%20wanted%20something%20else%20for%20the%20penultimate%20stage%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20my%20family%2C%20but%20they%20live%20across%20the%20US%20in%20places%20such%20as%20Texas%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Colorado.%20They%20want%20the%20best%20for%20me%2C%20as%20do%20my%20friends.%20Many%20of%20my%20NYC%20friends%20have%20left%20the%20city%2C%20and%20a%20few%20have%20passed%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202016%2C%20I've%20traveled%20to%20Europe%20several%20times%20a%20year%20to%20sing%20with%20a%20group.%20I%20particularly%20enjoyed%20the%20food%20and%20the%20general%20atmosphere%20in%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20like%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20live%20car-free%20in%20Paris.%20You%20can%20satisfy%20most%20of%20your%20basic%20needs%20within%2015%20minutes%20of%20home%20via%20walking%20or%20using%20public%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20to%20make%20friends%20during%20my%20visits%2C%20and%20the%20image%20of%20a%20permanent%20move%20crept%20into%20my%20mind.%20Some%20people%20said%20I%20was%20crazy%2C%20but%20I%20could%20either%20sit%20in%20New%20York%20fantasizing%20about%20France%20or%20I%20could%20take%20action.%20So%20I%20confronted%20my%20fantasy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20with%20a%20trial%20period%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20December%202019%2C%20I%20left%20to%20spend%20three%20months%20in%20Paris%20to%20decide%20whether%20I%20wanted%20to%20move%20permanently.%20I%20decided%20that%20I%20did%2C%20and%20I%20returned%20to%20New%20York%20to%20sell%20my%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20in%20March%202020%2C%20so%20the%20pandemic%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterrible%20real-estate%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20confined%20me%20to%20the%20city%20for%20almost%20another%20two%20years.%20Then%20the%20market%20revived%2C%20a%20buyer%20materialized%2C%20and%20in%20December%202021%2C%20I%20landed%20at%20Paris'%20Charles-de-Gaulle%20Airport%20to%20begin%20my%20new%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20selling%20my%20apartment%20in%20New%20York%2C%20I%20had%20to%20get%20a%20visa%2C%20arrange%20to%20ship%20my%20possessions%2C%20find%20lodging%20in%20Paris%2C%20and%20get%20the%20right%20COVID-19%20test.%20It%20was%20a%20full-time%20job%20for%20several%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDealing%20with%20complications%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20businesses%20exist%20specifically%20to%20help%20foreigners%20wrestle%20with%20these%20transitions.%20I%20found%20one%20in%20France%20and%20used%20its%20services%20whenever%20a%20process%20was%20extraordinarily%20daunting.%20Newness%20brings%20challenges%2C%20and%20I%20had%20plenty%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20visited%20France%2C%20read%20volumes%20in%20French%2C%20knew%20France's%20cultural%20icons%2C%20and%20spoke%20the%20language%20at%20a%20B2%20level%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20necessary%20fluency%20to%20communicate%20with%20native%20speakers%20without%20much%20effort%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there%20was%20still%20much%20to%20learn.%20You%20can%20never%20ask%20all%20the%20questions%20in%20advance%2C%20and%20many%20of%20my%20statements%20began%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20never%20occurred%20to%20me%20that%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20apartment%20was%20temporary%20and%20overpriced%2C%20in%20the%2016th%20arrondissement%20of%20Paris%2C%20where%20a%20guidebook%20said%20%26quot%3Ba%20feeling%20of%20luxury%2C%20or%20at%20least%20comfort%2C%20maintains.%26quot%3B%20When%20exiting%20the%20building%2C%20I%20could%20see%20the%20Eiffel%20Tower.%20It%20was%20lovely%2C%20but%20I%20was%20paying%20for%20the%20view%20and%20the%20classy%20address.%20I%20decided%20to%20look%20elsewhere%20%E2%80%94%20my%20rental%20agreement%20covered%20only%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20visiting%20websites%20and%20real-estate%20agents.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.french-property.com%2Fnews%2Ffrench_business%2Frenting_elderly_tenant_security_tenure%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelderly%20tenants%20have%20extra%20protection%20in%20France%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20landlords%20may%20hesitate%20to%20rent%20to%20them.%20Being%20in%20that%20category%2C%20I%20had%20to%20fend%20off%20hopelessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20learning%20continues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20I%20sold%20my%20New%20York%20apartment%20for%20a%20nice%20price%2C%20it%20wasn't%20enough%20for%20an%20appropriate%20place%20in%20Paris.%20I%20needed%20to%20get%20lucky%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20did.%20I%20found%20an%20apartment%20through%20a%20church%20buddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20into%20living%20in%20my%20current%20apartment%2C%20I%20had%20another%20surprise.%20One%20day%2C%20an%20officious%20tradesman%20came%20to%20my%20door%20unannounced%20to%20solicit%20my%20business%3A%20cleaning%20pipes%20in%20the%20kitchen.%20I%20said%20I%20didn't%20have%20the%20%E2%82%AC82%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20the%20work%20right%20then%20and%20there.%20A%20neighbor%20later%20told%20me%20that%20French%20law%20requires%20residents%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.french-property.com%2Fnews%2Fbuild_renovation_france%2Fboiler_maintainance_regulations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eream%20the%20pipelines%20of%20home-heating%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20annually%2C%20and%20I%20complied%20with%20a%20known%20vendor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dream%20of%20visiting%20Paris%20usually%20includes%20spending%20your%20days%20going%20to%20museums%20and%20having%20coffee%20at%20sidewalk%20caf%C3%A9s.%20I%20was%20spending%20my%20time%20finding%20the%20right%20laundry%20detergent%2C%20opening%20a%20bank%20account%2C%20and%20wrestling%20with%20tasks%20unknown%20to%20tourists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20I%20wanted%20baking%20soda%20to%20clean%20a%20sluggish%20drain.%20Not%20seeing%20it%20with%20the%20baking%20supplies%2C%20I%20asked%20a%20clerk%2C%20who%20pointed%20to%20the%20cleaning%20products.%20I%20later%20learned%20that%20there's%20cleaning-grade%20and%20food-grade%20baking%20soda%20in%20France.%20I%20wonder%20what%20would've%20happened%20had%20I%20used%20the%20former%20in%20a%20recipe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmbracing%20independence%20in%20France%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20New%20York%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20miss%20it.%20At%20this%20stage%20of%20my%20life%2C%20I%20want%20different%20things%2C%20and%20Paris%20offers%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20now%20have%20my%20residency%20card%20and%20my%20%26quot%3Bcarte%20vitale%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20accepts%20me%20into%20France's%20healthcare%20system.%20My%20current%20apartment%20lease%20ends%20in%20May%202024%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20exploring%20%26quot%3Bhabitat%20participatif%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20practice%20where%20a%20group%20of%20like-minded%20folks%20buys%20a%20building%20and%20lives%20together%20so%20each%20party%20has%20personal%20space%20yet%20enjoys%20common%20areas%20and%20shared%20amenities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-remote-jobs-more-productive-work-life-balance-return-office-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERemote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20makes%20my%20job%20as%20an%20independent%20contractor%20easier%2C%20but%20I'm%20wrestling%20with%20the%20tax%20implications%20for%20US%20citizens%20living%20abroad%20while%20working%20for%20US%20clients.%20Figuring%20out%20which%20tax%20deductions%20the%20French%20government%20allows%20has%20also%20raised%20questions%20I%20didn't%20know%20to%20ask%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommenting%20on%20New%20York%2C%20a%20writer%20once%20said%20that%20great%20cities%20make%20a%20deal%20with%20us%2C%20offering%20an%20experience%20like%20none%20other.%20In%20return%2C%20we%20agree%20not%20to%20complain.%20Settled%20in%20Paris%2C%20I%20spend%20my%20time%20responding%20to%20surprises%2C%20enjoying%20the%20pace%20of%20life%2C%20and%20digesting%20a%20lifetime%20of%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20turned%2080%20last%20November%2C%20and%20sometimes%20people%20ask%20whether%20I'm%20happy%20with%20the%20move.%20I%20answer%20that%20regret%20is%20not%20an%20option.%20You%20never%20have%20to%20do%20anything%20in%20life%2C%20except%20accept%20the%20consequences.%20I%20made%20a%20decision%20%E2%80%94%20my%20happiness%20depends%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20y