0Mehta%20replied.%20%E2%80%9CI%20gave%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20over%20the%20phone%20from%20Los%20Angeles%20two%20weeks%20ago.%20A%20very%20good%20interview%3B%20and%20I%20read%20it%2C%20it%20was%20verbatim%20perfect.%20The%20last%20sentence%20I%20told%20the%20man%2C%20and%20I%20met%20him%20recently%2C%20and%20he%20admitted%2C%20they%20took%20out%20the%20last%20thing%20I%20said%3A%20%E2%80%98I%20hope%20my%20Muslim%20friends%20can%20live%20in%20peace%20forever%20in%20India.%E2%80%99%20And%20that%20was%20not%20printed%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20was%20cut%20off%2C%20and%20the%20writer%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20give%20me%20a%20reason%20why.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20offend%20Mr%20Modi%20and%20the%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20Thapar%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20would%20that%20offend%20anybody%3F%20%E2%80%A6This%20morning%20I%20read%20that%20they%20were%20burning%20churches%20in%20Pakistan.%20One%20has%20to%20get%20over%20this%20madness%20of%20religious%20persecution.%20Hopefully%20things%20will%20change%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mehta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%20then%20went%20on%20to%20speak%20about%20the%20situation%20in%20Israel%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20hopes%20the%20government%20there%20will%20change%20very%20soon.%20The%20current%20situation%20there%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cis%20unbearable%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%E2%80%99s%20comment%20that%20he%20is%20referring%20to%20here%20did%20not%20appear%20in%20the%20print%20version%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20when%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20checked%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fhome%2Fsunday-times%2Fdont-underestimate-the-power-of-music%2Farticleshow%2F102588769.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eonline%20version%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%20(August%2021)%20at%2011%20am%2C%20the%20interview%20contained%20that%20quote.%3C%2Fp%3E